{"word":"ἐπεύχομαι","slug":"ἐπεύχομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπεύχομαι</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ξομαι</el>) </el><p/><a href='S:Deponent Verb, i.e. a Verb of Middle or Passive form with Active sense'>Dep.</a> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to pray</i> or <i>make a vow</i> to a deity, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to pray to</i> one <i>that . .</i> , <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a> :—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei, <i>to pray for</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>: also, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> cogn., <el>ἐπ. λιτάς</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to imprecate</i> a curse <i>upon</i>, <el>τί τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <el>ἐπεύχομαι [αὐτῷ] παθεῖν</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>: <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to utter imprecations</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><i>to glory over</i>, <el>τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>IV. </b><i>to boast that</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <b>Hhymn.</b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}